        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 4 at 8:13PM CDT by NWS Grand Forks ND</headline>
        <description>At 813 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Herrick, or 12 miles east of Grafton, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Drayton, Kennedy, Donaldson, Mattson, Bowesmont, Herrick, and Robbin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
